      <body>Q: Is it really intended that the created_at value can be overridden and set to any arbitrary date and time?  Does that not negate the entire purpose of the feature in AR?  I would think that rather than allowing updated_at to be similarly abused the real fix is to check to see if the current row is new and not whether the attribute created_at is already set.</body>
      <body-html>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Q: Is it really intended that the created_at value can be
overridden and set to any arbitrary date and time? Does that not
negate the entire purpose of the feature in AR? I would think that
rather than allowing updated_at to be similarly abused the real fix
is to check to see if the current row is new and not whether the
attribute created_at is already set.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</body-html>
